To my eyes there are three problems with Thoth, although I&#39;m sure there are many who would disagree with me.

1. Yo-yo looks too much like a capital P from T.O.  The top should be more rounded.
2. Eat slopes too far to the right.
3. Ha-ha should have a bit more curve to it -- more of a hook than a right angle.  However, I know that in my handwriting I rather deviate from the QM in this regard.  My ha-ha looks almost exactly like a mirror image of pipe -- QM doesn&#39;t do this.

I note that Kick looks in Thoth-font much the way I write it.  However, I think that the riser in Kick in the QM curves a little to the left.  I like the way it looks in Thoth-font, but it may not please someone who is more of a purist.

Thanks,
Greg

